		<h2>What does this app do?</h2>

		<p>
		    This app is really simple. We all like the cloud and <a href="http://www.getcloudapp.com/">CloudApp</a> especially. 
		    Our files on servers somewhere in the world and we can download them when ever and where ever we wish. But for those 
		    of you who like to keep a back-up of your data somewhere close, we've create a simple tool, which allows you to download 
		    all your data from <a href="http://www.getcloudapp.com/">CloudApp</a> as a single <strong>.zip</strong> archive.
		</p>
		<p>
		    <a href="http://www.getcloudapp.com/">CloudApp</a> is a brilliant service and the only thing you can't do with it is to 
		    download all your data at once. Well that is where this app comes into play.
		</p>
		<p>
		    With <a href="{$url}">CloudApp Downloader</a> all you do is just type in your 
		    <a href="http://www.getcloudapp.com">CloudApp</a> credentials (don't worry we don't store anything, we use 
		    <a href="http://www.getcloudapp.com/">CloudApp's</a> secure API), and our code does magically stuff and you will 
		    get a <strong>.zip</strong> archive with all your content. It is really that simple.
		</p>
